headline.main: PIONEER V UPSETS SUN FLARE THEORY; Satellite Still Transmitting Data, Space Aide Says -- Astronaut Plan Given

results.lead_paragraph: BOSTON, June 10 (AP) -- America's ninety-five-pound satellite Pioneer V, more than 14,000,000 miles from earth in an orbit around the sun, has given man new ideas about space, Hugh L. Dryden, deputy administrator of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration, said today.
